data.meta_description: Edgar Martínez (born January 2, 1963), nicknamed “Gar” and “Papi”. Puerto Rican, designated hitter and third baseman for the Seattle Mariners from 1987 through 2004. Teams Seattle Mariners (1987–2004) Career highlights and awards 7× All-Star (1992, 1995–1997, 2000, 2001, 2003) 5× Silver Slugger Award (1992, 1995, 1997, 2001, 2003) Roberto Clemente Award (2004) 2× AL batting champion (1992, 1995) AL RBI leader (2000) Seattle Mariners No. 11 retired Seattle Mariners Hall of Fame Hall of Fame 2019 […]

Description

Edgar Martínez

(born January 2, 1963), nicknamed “Gar” and “Papi”.

Puerto Rican, designated hitter and third baseman for the Seattle Mariners from 1987 through 2004.
